1.title: Family: Part 1
1.plot: Old friends and past companions gather to answer a question haunting them all - where is the Doctor?

2.title: Family: Part 2
2.plot: A powerful artifact reveals the Doctor's location, but is there any way his companions can reach him?

3.title: Family: Part 3
3.plot: The Doctor is condemned to death and his companions mount a rescue, unaware of the horrifying consequences.

4.title: Call of the Vocantem: Part 1
4.plot: Hunted by vengeful enemies, the Doctor takes refuge with powerful allies, but soon discovers that he has made a fatal mistake.

5.title: Call of the Vocantem: Part 2
5.plot: The Vocantem tighten their grip on the Doctor, forcing him and Ace to make one last stand.

6.title: The Silent Doll: Part 1
6.plot: An unstable mental patient may hold the key that the Doctor seeks to unravel a chilling mystery.

7.title: The Silent Doll: Part 2
7.plot: The Doctor struggles to rescue Ace from a vicious parasite, without becoming its next victim.

8.title: Nightmare on the Boulevard: Part 1
8.plot: The Doctor and Ace tour Hollywood, but find themselves lured into the snare of a brutal new film studio.

9.title: Nightmare on the Boulevard: Part 2
9.plot: The search for Hollywood's last director leads Ace into a battle for her life, whilst the Doctor faces off against a merciless producer.

10.title: Dark Shadow: Part 1
10.plot: The Doctor and Ace visit a space station where thoughts become reality, but the secrets within the Doctor's mind unleash an unstoppable terror.

11.title: Dark Shadow: Part 2
11.plot: As the creature's power becomes absolute, the Doctor realises there is only one way to defeat it.

1.title: Prisoners of Arriton: Part 1
1.plot: The planets of the Arriton system have mysteriously vanished, save for Arriton II. The Doctor and Ace investigate, only to discover they are not alone.

2.title: Prisoners of Arriton: Part 2
2.plot: Now captives of the Daleks, the Doctor and Ace soon realise they are not the only prisoners on Arriton II, but what secrets lie within an abandoned shipwreck?

3.title: Prisoners of Arriton: Part 3
3.plot: In a desperate effort to save a dying race, the Doctor subverts the Laws of Time. But can he stop the Daleks from repeating history?

4.title: The Tombs of Ice: Part 1
4.plot: The TARDIS crash lands on a barren ice world and the Doctor locates forgotten cryogenic tombs, whilst Ace discovers that not everyone on the planet is frozen.

5.title: The Tombs of Ice: Part 2
5.plot: The Sontarans awake from a long sleep to discover that time has passed them by, but they intend to complete their lethal mission.

6.title: The Tombs of Ice: Part 3
6.plot: The Doctor and Ace work with a new ally in hopes of preventing the Sontarans from destroying the entire galaxy.

7.title: Rise of the Sea Devils: Part 1
7.plot: The TARDIS materialises on a nuclear submarine deep in the ocean. The crew is missing, an assault is underway, and the Doctor recognises the invaders.

8.title: Rise of the Sea Devils: Part 2
8.plot: The Sea Devils take control of the submarine, intent on using its nuclear weapons in an ongoing war. Can the Doctor stop them from unleashing Armageddon?

9.title: Rise of the Sea Devils: Part 3
9.plot: The Sea Devils' base comes under siege as the Doctor learns exactly whom they are fighting against.

10.title: The Secret Warrior: Part 1
10.plot: The Doctor and Ace arrive on a space station within the eye of Jupiter only to find themselves accused of murder.

11.title: The Secret Warrior: Part 2
11.plot: Deep within the space station Ace finds dormant Ice Warriors and a guardian who will protect them at any cost, but an even stronger threat approaches.

12.title: The Secret Warrior: Part 3
12.plot: The Ice Lord's attempt to revive his future warriors erupts in a chain reaction that could destroy Jupiter and everyone on board the station.

13.title: Siege of the Cybermen: Part 1
13.plot: Two Cybermen invade the TARDIS and shoot Ace. Can a journey to Telos save her life?

14.title: Siege of the Cybermen: Part 2
14.plot: The Doctor hides a dying Ace in Charlie's workshop on Telos, but can he trust an old Cyberman to heal her?

15.title: Siege of the Cybermen: Part 3
15.plot: Ace lives, but Edgar the old Cyberman rejoins his fellow Cyber Units and swears to destroy the Doctor.

16.title: The Time Assassin: Part 1
16.plot: Gallifrey is plucked out of space and time, and the Time Lords find themselves under threat of death from the brutal Time Assassin.

17.title: The Time Assassin: Part 2
17.plot: The Doctor and K-9 attempt to lure the Time Assassin into a trap and locate the stolen Time Scoop, but this plan reveals a greater danger.

18.title: The Time Assassin: Part 3
18.plot: The Doctor ventures into Rassilon's Tomb in hopes of recovering the Time Scoop, but activating its power may be a terrible mistake.

19.title: The Time Assassin: Part 4
19.plot: The Time Assassin makes his final move and the Doctor soon realises the killer is but a pawn in a far deadlier scheme, one that costs Ace dearly.

20.title: Domination of the Daleks: Part 1 (Xmas Special)
20.plot: Davros captures the Doctor and unveils his master plan for the Time Scoop and his armies of Daleks.

21.title: Domination of the Daleks: Part 2 (Xmas Special)
21.plot: The Daleks begin their conquest as the Doctor issues Davros with an ultimatum, whilst every life on Gallifrey hangs in the balance.

1.title: A Fear of the Fair: Part 1
1.plot: It's fun and games of the deadliest sort as the TARDIS is hijacked and the Doctor ends up at the mercy of a whimsical foe.

2.title: A Fear of the Fair: Part 2
2.plot: The Celestial Toymaker intends to spend his final years with the perfect plaything -- the Doctor.

3.title: A Fear of the Fair: Part 3
3.plot: The Doctor gambles with the TARDIS and his very life as he allows the Toymaker on board, and finds a new companion in the mind-altering Domino.

4.title: The Killing Breed: Part 1
4.plot: The TARDIS responds to a distress call and the Doctor comes to the aid of Silurians living on a distant planet, but what are their true intentions?

5.title: The Killing Breed: Part 2
5.plot: The Doctor and Domino encounter the Neo-Silurians, genetically enhanced clones who believe the Doctor is their greatest weapon.

6.title: The Killing Breed: Part 3
6.plot: The Doctor finds himself caught between the Silurians and their violent offspring, who clash in a final battle for supremacy.

7.title: The Uprising: Part 1
7.plot: The Doctor and Domino arrive on Venus in the distant future, only to discover a mining colony suffering under the thumb of a ruthless dictator.

8.title: The Uprising: Part 2
8.plot: Tetrap slaves rebel against the cruel dictatorship, whilst the Doctor becomes a hunted man.

9.title: The Uprising: Part 3
9.plot: Tetraps plan the ultimate revenge against all humanity, but the dictator has yet to surrender.

10.title: The Human Nexus: Part 1
10.plot: An attack on a human colony leads the Doctor and Domino to the planet Devron, where the colonists may already be victims.

11.title: The Human Nexus: Part 2
11.plot: The sinister Botcheen take the Doctor inside the Nexus, where they reveal the truth about its tremendous powers.

12.title: The Human Nexus: Part 3
12.plot: The Doctor must stop the Botcheen from taking control of the Nexus, but he stumbles across a far more dangerous secret..

13.title: The Dalek Trap: Part 1
13.plot: A traveling merchant tortures a group of Daleks into servitude, but the Doctor suspects they are far from defeated.

14.title: The Dalek Trap: Part 2
14.plot: Domino takes pity on one of the enslaved Daleks, and soon the Doctor enters into a no-win scenario against a murderous opponent.

15.title: The Dalek Trap: Part 3
15.plot: The Doctor faces off against the rogue Dalek, and desperately tries to save Domino from paying the ultimate price.

16.title: Revenge of the Timelord: Part 1
16.plot: The Master has returned and taken control of the TARDIS. His next target - the Doctor.

17.title: Revenge of the Timelord: Part 2
17.plot: The Doctor discovers who created the Nexus, but his efforts to outwit the Master lead to a deadly confrontation.

18.title: Revenge of the Timelord: Part 3
18.plot: The Doctor struggles to prevent the Master from dominating all of time and space with the Nexus, but powerful forces are at work against them both.

19.title: Fourth Night: Part 1 (Halloween Special)
19.plot: The Fourth Doctor and K-9 join the Seventh Doctor on a voyage into England's past, and a close encounter with the notorious Guy Fawkes.

20.title: Fourth Night: Part 2 (Halloween Special)
20.plot: The Mandragora Helix and its disciples close in on the two Doctors. Is the Gunpowder Plot their only hope of survival?

21.title: The Angel in the Attic: Part 1 (Xmas Special)
21.plot: A strange force pulls the TARDIS to an old mansion where the Doctor finds both trapped inhabitants and relentless predators.

22.title: The Angel in the Attic: Part 2 (Xmas Special)
22.plot: With the Weeping Angels all around them, the Doctor, Guy Fawkes, and Maria discover there is no escape from the old mansion.

1.title: The Prediction of the Seer: Part 1
1.plot: The universe is at war, the Matrix is off-line, and the Doctor's only hope of stopping the conflict may be a mad prophet in the caves of Gallifrey.

2.title: The Prediction of the Seer: Part 2
2.plot: The Seer is missing, Gallifrey is under attack, and the Doctor's TARDIS gets underway - without him.

3.title: The Prediction of the Seer: Part 3
3.plot: The Doctor struggles to recover the TARDIS and prevent catastrophic damage to the timeline, whilst the Seer gazes into a grim future.

4.title: The God of War: Part 1
4.plot: A trip to Egypt in the 1920's leads the Doctor and Maria to the excavation of an ancient tomb, and the revival of a vengeful enemy.

5.title: The God of War: Part 2
5.plot: The War Lord is free and vows to destroy those who have imprisoned him, beginning with the Doctor.

6.title: The God of War: Part 3
6.plot: As the War Lord's power becomes absolute, the Doctor throws himself and the TARDIS into one last effort to stop the War Lord from absorbing Earth.

7.title: Cyberspace: Part 1
7.plot: Children on Earth are disappearing without a trace; could a mysterious new Internet browser be the cause?

8.title: Cyberspace: Part 2
8.plot: With Maria kidnapped, the Doctor enters Cyberspace to mount a rescue. However, he may be the very prisoner the Cybermen need.

9.title: Cyberspace: Part 3
9.plot: With their new planet the Cybermen prepare to conquer the galaxy, but the Universal War has found them. Can the Doctor and Maria escape Cyberspace alive?

10.title: Infection: Part 1
10.plot: The Doctor and Maria land on a prison ship carrying both a deadly disease and a corrupt scientist who will stop at nothing to control it.

11.title: Infection: Part 2
11.plot: Maria is infected with the Naenara virus. Will the Doctor collaborate with the Rani to find a cure?

12.title: Infection: Part 3
12.plot: The Doctor engages the Rani in a high-stakes bargain for Maria's life, but is he too late to stop the virus from killing his companion?

13.title: The Naenara Disaster: Part 1
13.plot: The key to winning the Universal War is locating the hidden Naenara vessel. Can the Doctor reach it before the Sontarans?

14.title: The Naenara Disaster: Part 2
14.plot: The Sontarans control the deadliest weapon in the universe, and they intend to unleash its fury upon the Doctor.

15.title: The Naenara Disaster: Part 3
15.plot: The Doctor and Maria fight to contain the Naenara vessel before its detonation spreads the plague across the galaxy.

16.title: War's End: Part 1
16.plot: The Universal War rages beyond all control, whilst the Doctor discovers that time travel itself is at risk.

17.title: War's End: Part 2
17.plot: As the Doctor confronts the cause of the Universal War, the Lord President employs his own strategy to defend Gallifrey.

18.title: War's End: Part 3
18.plot: Battle fleets surround the Time Lords as the Doctor and Rassilon join forces in a final attempt to save the universe.

19.title: Acquisition of the Daleks: Part 1 (Xmas Special)
19.plot: Rassilon sends the Doctor on a quest to recover his TARDIS and restore the Time Vortex, but the Daleks intend to become the new masters of time.

20.title: Acquisition of the Daleks: Part 2 (Xmas Special)
20.plot: Davros schemes to steal Rassilon's TARDIS or crack the universe in two, forcing the Doctor to make a horrific choice.

1.title: Generation X: Part 1
1.plot: The Doctor and Maria investigate fatal attacks on board a luxury space station, where plastic is the latest shopping trend.

2.title: Generation X: Part 2
2.plot: The Doctor uncovers a chilling secret lurking within the station's shops, a secret that will change every patron forever.

3.title: Generation X: Part 3
3.plot: The war between the Nestene and the Plastonians explodes, putting the entire station in jeopardy.

4.title: Prophecy of the Daleks: Part 1
4.plot: The Doctor and the Daleks converge on an ore refinery that holds the key to repairing Rassilon's TARDIS.

5.title: Prophecy of the Daleks: Part 2
5.plot: The Daleks begin a full-scale assault on the refinery, but the Doctor faces a closer threat from the treacherous Foreman.

6.title: Prophecy of the Daleks: Part 3
6.plot: The Doctor engages the Foreman in a battle of wits as the Daleks invade the refinery.

7.title: Heaven: Part 1
7.plot: The Doctor and Maria visit Heaven, a cemetery for dead races, where Maria encounters a shocking vision behind a church door.

8.title: Heaven: Part 2
8.plot: Maria's thoughts resurrect her brother, whilst a cunning priest schemes to bring his entire race back to life, but can the ancient device causing the miracles be controlled?

9.title: Heaven: Part 3
9.plot: As restored races flood Heaven, the Doctor retreats into the TARDIS, but can he stop a madman from unleashing an even more dreadful horror?

10.title: Cold Equations: Part 1
10.plot: The Doctor finds himself stranded on a frozen world, a planet in desperate need of his help.

11.title: Cold Equations: Part 2
11.plot: Surrounded by questions and vicious barbarians, the Doctor delves into the mystery of a missing people.

12.title: Cold Equations: Part 3
12.plot: The Doctor searches for his lost TARDIS and revives the sirens, but who exactly are they?

13.title: Decree of the Daleks: Part 1
13.plot: To reach Rassilon's TARDIS, the Doctor and Maria must smuggle themselves onto a Dalek prison planet.

14.title: Decree of the Daleks: Part 2
14.plot: The Doctor and Maria arrive on Kembel, but find the planet - and the Daleks - deadly as ever.

15.title: Decree of the Daleks: Part 3
15.plot: Maria and the Doctor uncover a dark secret within the TARDIS of Rassilon.

16.title: Time of the Doctor: Part 1
16.plot: The Parakind are free and vow to punish the one Time Lord who dared to confine them.

17.title: Time of the Doctor: Part 2
17.plot: With the Daleks and the Parakind closing in on Gallifrey, the Doctor and Maria become embroiled in Rassilon's end game.

18.title: Time of the Doctor: Part 3
18.plot: Rassilon hatches his plot, the Parakind lash out at their tormentor, and the Doctor makes a crucial sacrifice to restore the Time Vortex.

1.title: The Mystery of Cell 882: Part 1
1.plot: The Eighth Doctor's journey to recover his other incarnations begins. The Ninth Doctor finds himself locked up on the prison planet Inferno 161, and his cell mate Cigam warns him that escape is impossible.

2.title: The Mystery of Cell 882: Part 2
2.plot: With Cigam in control of the TARDIS, The Eighth Doctor is trapped on Inferno 161, but he is not alone. Meanwhile on board the TARDIS, Maria begins a fight for her life that will end with a revelation about her very being.

3.title: Heart of Steel: Part 1
3.plot: Whilst the Eighth Doctor searches the universe for his lost incarnations, the Sixth Doctor faces upgrading at the hands of the Cybermen, but help may be closer than he thinks.

4.title: Heart of Steel: Part 2
4.plot: With the aid of a new ally, the Sixth Doctor attempts to thwart the Cybermen's invasion plans. Soon, however, the Sixth Doctor becomes a hunted man, targeted for death.

5.title: Heart of Steel: Part 3
5.plot: The Sixth Doctor and his new ally put their bold strategy into action, but the Cyber Controller stands in their way, as does a far more unexpected foe.

6.title: The Lost Souls: Part 1
6.plot: The Second Doctor finds himself in an abandoned mental asylum - or is it? Soon he uncovers brutal experiments in which he may become the next victim.

7.title: The Lost Souls: Part 2
7.plot: The Second and Eighth Doctors struggle to rescue the asylum patients from certain doom, as Maria desperately tries to prevent the Doctor's death...

8.title: The Lost Souls: Part 3
8.plot: The Second and Eighth Doctors are on the run, whilst Maria falls prey to the asylum's sinister Director, who will stop at nothing to gain what he seeks...

9.title: The Jekyll Syndrome: Part 1
9.plot: The Fourth Doctor attempts to diffuse a rocket warhead in the midst of a bloody rebellion on an Earth colony, but he remains unaware of the rocket's true, darker purpose.

10.title: The Jekyll Syndrome: Part 2
10.plot: The Fourth Doctor and Maria take refuge in the war-torn ruins as Earth soldiers and rebels - now united with a single mission - capture the Eighth Doctor as a prisoner of war.

11.title: The Jekyll Syndrome: Part 3
11.plot: The Fourth and Eighth Doctors find themselves trapped as their enemies close in. Will they risk the death of all their incarnations, or surrender their most vital asset.

12.title: Falcon's Touch: Part 1
12.plot: The Fifth Doctor bargains with an alien merchant in hopes of finding his lost TARDIS, but instead discovers the merchant is selling the deadliest substance in the universe.

13.title: Falcon's Touch: Part 2
13.plot: The Fifth and Eighth Doctors combine forces to do battle with a toxic menace that threatens to destroy the galaxy, yet their victory could lead to a far greater defeat.

14.title: Falcon's Touch: Part 3
14.plot: Maria attempts to negotiate with an enemy that grows ever more powerful, as the Eighth Doctor realises that he must make a terrible sacrifice.

15.title: One: Part 1
15.plot: The First Doctor rescues the lone survivor of a shipwreck on a desolate asteroid, but he soon discovers they are not alone.

16.title: One: Part 2
16.plot: The First Doctor and Erasmus explore the mysterious tunnels inside the asteroid, as the Eighth Doctor and Maria find themselves surrounded by the Cyber Fleet.

17.title: One: Part 3
17.plot: The Cyber Fleet launches an all-out assault on the asteroid as the First and Eighth Doctors defend themselves, whilst Maria faces the Cyber Conglomerate.

18.title: Scream of the Cybermen: Part 1
18.plot: The Seventh Doctor assists the Eighth as they unravel the secrets of the asteroid and evade the clutches of invading Cyber Legions.

19.title: Scream of the Cybermen: Part 2
19.plot: The reunited Seventh Doctor and Maria confront the Cyber Conglomerate, whilst the Eighth Doctor must contend with the Cyber Fleet.

20.title: Scream of the Cybermen: Part 3
20.plot: The Eighth Doctor battles the Cyber Controller as the Seventh Doctor struggles against the Cyber Conglomerate, and Maria must choose which Doctor to save.

21.title: The Father of Time: Part 1
21.plot: Using the Doctor's own life force, Omega travels back into Gallifrey's past to stop himself from making Time Lord history - but at what cost for both the Doctor and the planet?

22.title: The Father of Time: Part 2
22.plot: Omega's grip on the past grows stronger, and the Doctor must defend his own place in history.

23.title: ONE FINE TIME LORD
23.plot: "HISTORY WILL BE WRITTEN" The Archeron Trilogy begins.

1.title: Possession: Part 1
1.plot: The Doctor and his new companion find themselves drawn into a crumbling temple on a lost world, where a former ally and a vicious enemy await.

2.title: Possession: Part 2
2.plot: The Doctor is reborn with powers beyond anything he's ever known, but can he manage these new abilities or will his darker impulses take control?

3.title: Possession: Part 3
3.plot: An invincible new life form rises up and lays claim to the power of the Guardians, with the intent of making the Doctor and Perdita his first victims.

4.title: Proclamation: Part 1
4.plot: A distress call sends the Doctor far into Earth's future, where he finds London in ruins, a creature on the rampage, and an old friend in urgent need of help.

5.title: Proclamation: Part 2
5.plot: The search is on to locate the mysterious Hall of Proclamations, but the Doctor and UNIT face competition from the Daleks and a toxic beast even the Daleks fear.

6.title: Proclamation: Part 3
6.plot: The hideous creature reveals its true nature and the Doctor discovers the Hall of Proclamations, but can he stop the Daleks from plundering its secrets?

7.title: Run: Part 1
7.plot: The TARDIS goes berserk and hurtles itself towards a blazing hot star, with the Doctor and Perdita desperately trying to survive as the ship erupts into flames.

8.title: Run: Part 2
8.plot: The Doctor and Perdita struggle to avoid both deadly fires and a giant leech that threatens to drain them to dust as they attempt to save the TARDIS and themselves.

9.title: Run: Part 3
9.plot: The Doctor battles the Universal Guardian for control of the TARDIS, whilst Perdita finds herself trapped by a relentless killer.

10.title: Betrayal: Part 1
10.plot: The Doctor and Perdita clash over how to combat the Daleks' latest planetary invasion, forcing Perdita to take drastic action.

11.title: Betrayal: Part 2
11.plot: Perdita leads an assault force against the Dalek Fleet, whilst the Doctor learns a shocking truth about his companion.

12.title: Betrayal: Part 3
12.plot: The Doctor finds himself torn between protecting a defenceless world from the Daleks and rescuing Perdita, who must fight the Universal Guardian.

13.title: Sacrifice: Part 1
13.plot: The Doctor refuses to kill the Universal Guardian, until he realises that to save the universe from the Daleks he has no other choice.

14.title: Sacrifice: Part 2
14.plot: The Doctor seeks out the one person from his past who can destroy the Universal Guardian, but the Daleks will stop at nothing to prevent their reunion.

15.title: Sacrifice: Part 3
15.plot: As the Daleks lay siege to Gallifrey, the Doctor enters a final conflict with the Universal Guardian and a dark prophecy comes to pass.

16.title: DARK TIMES
16.plot: "A SHADOW DESCENDS" The Archeron Trilogy continues.

imdb.plot outline: Join the new voyages of the Seventh Doctor as he journeys through time and space! Following the events of "Survival", the final story of the Classic Series, Doctor Who Online Adventures picks up with the intrepid Time Lord and his amazing TARDIS as they visit eras long past and futures yet to be. The Doctor's incredible travels through the cosmos continue as he encounters new allies and struggles against old enemies, protects desperate worlds and defies ruthless tyrants, battles terrifying aliens and aids vulnerable cultures, all whilst combating galactic invasions and defending the universe he loves. The Doctor's ongoing saga unfolds in Doctor Who Online Adventures!
imdb.title: Doctor Who Online Adventures
plot: Follow the Doctor on his incredible journeys across the universe and throughout time. Enter the TARDIS and travel with the Doctor as he protects the innocent, challenges the mighty, and defends the cosmos from any and all forms of evil.::M. Justin Parsons

Join the new voyages of the Seventh Doctor as he journeys through time and space! Following the events of "Survival", the final story of the Classic Series, _Doctor Who Online Adventures_ (qv) picks up with the intrepid Time Lord and his amazing TARDIS as they visit eras long past and futures yet to be. The Doctor's incredible travels through the cosmos continue as he encounters new allies and struggles against old enemies, protects desperate worlds and defies ruthless tyrants, battles terrifying aliens and aids vulnerable cultures, all whilst combating galactic invasions and defending the universe he loves. The Doctor's ongoing saga unfolds in _Doctor Who Online Adventures_ (qv)!::M. Justin Parsons
synopsis: After the events of the 1989 serial Survival: The adventures of the Seventh Doctor continues on as he travels through time and space in his Type 40 Tardis and with the aid of his companions and his follow race, The Time Lords, he continues to save the universe from evil forces thought the cosmos, however life with the Doctor is never easy, when loosing his companion Ace to the power of the Daleks, the Doctor sets out to discover the mystery's revolving around him thought time and space, who is the time assassin and who's he working for, what is the Nexus and its strange connection with rest of the universe, what is the Naenara and why does everyone what it, and why has the vortex been destroyed, can it be fixed and if so at what cost.
